{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"059f14f7-6ae9-48ef-be8f-175f7a21dd3e","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n1. **Update NuGet packages** in your `.csproj`:\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`\n   - Update `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v5.0.0+** (it bundles Microsoft.Testing.Platform support)\n   - Add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TestReports` if you need TRX/code-coverage reports\n\n2. **Add the MSBuild property** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable the test runner** (pick one approach):\n   - **Property (recommended):**\n     ```xml\n     <PropertyGroup>\n       <GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>true</GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>\n     </PropertyGroup>\n     ```\n   - **Or** add a `Program.cs` entry point manually (rarely needed).\n\n4. **Run tests** the same way:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- NUnit3TestAdapter **v5+** is required; 4.6.0 does not support Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n- `dotnet test` works with the new platform when `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is set.\n- If you use `dotnet vstest` or `.runsettings` features, review them — some VSTest-specific options differ on the new platform.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1b0aaafc-65c7-4377-9849-812279d83eda","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a general knowledge question - I don't need to look at any specific files. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":440,"requestId":"4C24:1414DF:D6664B:10A4DAB:6A012963"},"id":"8820526a-2c91-4767-ad75-1dbabecb0d25","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:57:17.647Z","parentId":"43825239-14f5-4a34-a806-ee4ccf82c960"}
